// So, first, we parse the string into an AST of extglobs, without turning
// anything into regexps yet.
//
// ['a', {@ [['i'], ['w', {!['x', 'y']}, 'z'], ['j']]}, 'b']
//
// Then, for all the negative extglobs, we append whatever comes after in
// each parent as their tail
//
// ['a', {@ [['i'], ['w', {!['x', 'y'], 'z', 'b'}, 'z'], ['j']]}, 'b']
//
